{"source_hash": "3541d4bed9bb45c0", "candidate": {"id": "cand-019", "name": "Ananya Krishnan", "raw_cv": "ANANYA KRISHNAN\nananya.krishnan@email.com | Cambridge, UK\n\nML ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nML engineer with 4 years of experience in audio and signal processing ML systems, transitioning into computer vision. Proficient in Python and PyTorch. Experience with MLflow and production model deployment.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nML Engineer \u2014 Sonos, Cambridge (2021\u2013present)\n- Built and deployed audio classification models for Sonos device wake-word and noise cancellation features\n- Developed training pipelines in PyTorch and managed experiments with MLflow\n- Optimised models for embedded deployment using ONNX and quantisation techniques\n- Collaborated with hardware team on latency and memory budgets\n\nGraduate ML Engineer \u2014 BT Research, Ipswich (2020\u20132021)\n- Developed speech quality assessment models for VoIP network monitoring\n\nSKILLS\nPython, PyTorch, ONNX, MLflow, NumPy, librosa, torchaudio, OpenCV (basic), Git, Docker\n\nEDUCATION\nMSc Acoustic Engineering \u2014 University of Southampton (2019\u20132020)\nBEng Electronic Engineering \u2014 University of Southampton (2016\u20132019)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen (Indian heritage)", "raw_linkedin": "ML engineer at Sonos building audio intelligence systems. Four years of experience in deep learning for audio \u2014 wake word detection, noise cancellation, speech quality. Strong PyTorch and ONNX skills, significant experience with embedded deployment and latency optimisation. Cambridge-based. Interested in broadening into computer vision and sensor-based perception systems. Open to roles in defence, IoT, or robotics.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Ananya, your audio ML background is interesting \u2014 how do you see yourself adapting to optical and radar-based perception?\n\nAnanya: The engineering fundamentals are very similar \u2014 both involve signal processing, CNN-based feature extraction, and hard latency constraints for embedded deployment. I've been actively studying computer vision: I completed the Stanford CS231n materials last year and I've been working on a personal project with object detection on edge hardware. My audio expertise gives me a strong foundation in signal processing that's directly relevant to radar.\n\nInterviewer: How do you feel about the hybrid setup? Two days in Cambridge.\n\nAnanya: Perfect. I live in Cambridge, I actually cycle to Sonos's office already. The hybrid model would work very well.\n\nInterviewer: Security clearance \u2014 do you hold any clearance?\n\nAnanya: I don't hold formal clearance currently. I've worked on some BT Research projects that involved government contracts with data handling agreements, but nothing that required formal SC or DV vetting. I'm a UK citizen, no dual nationality, no foreign connections \u2014 I'd expect to be eligible for clearance.\n\nInterviewer: We can sponsor that. Salary?\n\nAnanya: I'm at \u00a372,000 at Sonos. I'm looking for \u00a380\u201390,000 for this step, given the domain stretch and the defence sector context.", "years_experience": 4.0, "skills": ["Python", "PyTorch", "ONNX", "MLflow", "NumPy", "librosa", "torchaudio", "OpenCV", "Git", "Docker", "signal processing", "audio classification", "embedded deployment", "quantisation", "CNNs", "object detection", "computer vision"], "industries": ["audio technology", "defence", "IoT", "robotics", "telecom", "embedded systems"], "seniority_level": "mid", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "master", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.85, "culture_fit_score": 0.82, "constraints": [{"id": "640c5d2a", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary at Sonos \u00a372,000 (baseline reference from interview)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 72000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "4e3162d6", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Minimum salary expectation \u00a380,000 for next role (interview transcript)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 80000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95}, {"id": "f8a3fb57", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Target salary range upper bound \u00a390,000 (interview transcript)", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 90000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9}, {"id": "35335ad2", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Prefers hybrid setup: 2 days in Cambridge office (interview transcript)", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 2.0, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.93}, {"id": "98a8e938", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Lives in Cambridge, cycles to current office; location preference for Cambridge (CV and interview)", "canonical_key": "location_city", "value": "Cambridge", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95}, {"id": "cfc21810", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "security", "description": "No formal clearance currently held, but UK citizen with no dual nationality or foreign connections \u2014 eligible for SC/DV vetting. Employer willing to sponsor (interview transcript)", "canonical_key": "security_clearance", "value": "eligible", "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88}, {"id": "28a8fee7", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "career", "description": "Interested in defence sector roles and domain expansion; willing to transition from audio to perception systems (interview and LinkedIn)", "canonical_key": "industry_background", "value": "defence", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.82}, {"id": "71bf46e3", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "skills", "description": "Actively transi